Description: Landscape with the flight into Egypt, with at the right Mary holding the Child seated on a donkey, which is being led by Joseph past three small trees; in the background a lake, mountains, and in the middle ground a cart being hauled by two oxen. c.1580s Engraving
Curator's comments: Presumably a north Italian composition, in the wake of Titian's landscapes.
Acquisition notes: The 208 items in the 1950 purchase from the Liechtenstein collection consisted of Italian prints. They were views of Rome; prints after Titian; portraits of Roman Emperors; and various other prints after Venetian artists.
